tRingMgmtRingName.name: tRingMgmtRingName
tRingMgmtRingName.description: The ASCII name assigned to this ring. This name defaults to 'Network n', where n is a unique integer value from 1 to n.

tRingMgmtStnPortCount.name: tRingMgmtStnPortCount
tRingMgmtStnPortCount.description: Returns the total number of physical ports on this ring which may be controlled by this device.

tRingMgmtRingPortCount.name: tRingMgmtRingPortCount
tRingMgmtRingPortCount.description: Returns the total number of ring in/out ports on this ring which may be controlled by this device.

tRingMgmtStnPortsEnable.name: tRingMgmtStnPortsEnable
tRingMgmtStnPortsEnable.description: Setting this object to enable will cause all the station ports on the ring which may be controlled by this device to be enabled. Setting this object to noEnable will have no effect. When read this object will always return noEnable.

tRingMgmtRingPortsEnable.name: tRingMgmtRingPortsEnable
tRingMgmtRingPortsEnable.description: Setting this object to enable will cause all the ring in/out ports on the ring which may be controlled by this device to be enabled. Setting this object to noEnable will have no effect. When read this object will always return noEnable.

tRingMgmtStnPortsOn.name: tRingMgmtStnPortsOn
tRingMgmtStnPortsOn.description: Returns the total number of enabled station ports on this ring which may be controlled by this device.

tRingMgmtRingPortsOn.name: tRingMgmtRingPortsOn
tRingMgmtRingPortsOn.description: Returns the total number of enabled ring in/out ports on this ring which may be controlled by this device.

tRingMgmtStations.name: tRingMgmtStations
tRingMgmtStations.description: Returns the number of stations currently inserted on the ring, if known (includes this device). If not known, returns zero.

tRingMgmtRingState.name: tRingMgmtRingState
tRingMgmtRingState.description: Returns the operational state of the ring, if known.

tRingMgmtRingSpeed.name: tRingMgmtRingSpeed
tRingMgmtRingSpeed.description: Returns the ring speed of the ring, if known. The speed is designated by the value returned: unknown..............0 fourMegaBits.........4 sixteenMegaBits.....16

tRingMgmtActiveMonitor.name: tRingMgmtActiveMonitor
tRingMgmtActiveMonitor.description: Returns the address of the active monitor on this ring, if known. If unknown, the NULL address (00-00-00-00-00-00) is returned.

tRingMgmtRingNumber.name: tRingMgmtRingNumber
tRingMgmtRingNumber.description: A read of this object returns the ring number of the attached ring. If the ring number is indeterminate, a zero is returned.

tRingMgmtBeaconRecovery.name: tRingMgmtBeaconRecovery
tRingMgmtBeaconRecovery.description: This object controls the operation of beacon recovery. A write of disable to this object will cause the beacon recovery process to become inactive on this host. A write of enable will cause the beacon recovery process to become active. If beacon recovery is inoperable on the managing device this object will return 'BADSETINFO'. A read of this object will return the current value of this object, reflecting either the last request made or, in the case of a device which is unable to manage beacon recovery, invalid. This object either defaults to enabled or invalid, depending on whether the device can or cannot manage beacon recovery.

tRingMgmtBcnRecRingPortRetryCount.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecRingPortRetryCount
tRingMgmtBcnRecRingPortRetryCount.description: This object defines the number of times a token ring ring port will be re-enabled after it has been determined that the port is causing the ring to beacon. Values other than 0-100 and 999 will result in MIB bad value. Default of object is product dependent. Refer to individual product documentation. Valid integer values are defined as: 0 ...disable ring port retries 1 - 100 ...retry ring port n times 999 ... retry ring port infinite times

tRingMgmtBcnRecRingPortRetryDelay.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecRingPortRetryDelay
tRingMgmtBcnRecRingPortRetryDelay.description: This object defines the time delay between disabling a token ring ring port due to beaconing and re-enabling the port to check the state of the ring port. Setting this object to zero disables retry queue. Non-zero value is delay in seconds. Some products have resolutions that will round this value (in seconds) to the nearest multiple of 7 seconds. Default of object is product dependent. Refer to individual product documentation.

tRingMgmtBcnRecStnPortRetryCount.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecStnPortRetryCount
tRingMgmtBcnRecStnPortRetryCount.description: This object defines the number of times a token ring station port will be re-enabled after it has been determined that the port is causing the ring to beacon. Values other than 0-100 and 999 will result in MIB bad value. Default of object is product dependent. Refer to individual product documentation. Valid integer values are defined as: 0 ...disable station port retries 1 - 100 ...retry station port n times 999 ... retry station port infinite times

tRingMgmtBcnRecStnPortRetryDelay.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecStnPortRetryDelay
tRingMgmtBcnRecStnPortRetryDelay.description: This object defines the time delay between disabling a token ring station port due to beaconing and re-enabling the port to check the state of the station port. Setting this object to zero disables retry queue. Non-zero value is delay in seconds. Some products have resolutions that will round this value (in seconds) to the nearest multiple of 7 seconds. Default of object is product dependent. Refer to individual product documentation.

tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdBypassRetryCount.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdBypassRetryCount
tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdBypassRetryCount.description: This object defines the number of times a token ring MIM board, having been bypassed by beacon recovery, will be un-bypassed to determine if the MIM board is causing the ring to beacon. Values other than 0-100 and 999 will result in MIB bad value. Valid integer values are defined as: 0 ...disable MIM bypass retries 1 - 100 ...retry MIM board un-bypass n times 999 ...retry MIM board un-bypass infinite times Default value is 1.

tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdBypassRetryDelay.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdBypassRetryDelay
tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdBypassRetryDelay.description: This object defines the time delay between bypassing a token ring MIM board due to beaconing and re-enabling the MIM board to check the state of the board. Setting this object to zero disables retry queue. Non-zero value is delay in seconds with a delay resolution of 1 second.

tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdWrapRetryCount.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdWrapRetryCount
tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdWrapRetryCount.description: This object defines the number of times a token ring MIM board, having been wrapped left or right by beacon recovery, will be un-wrapped to determine if the MIM board is causing the ring to beacon. Values other than 0-100 and 999 will result in MIB bad value. Valid integer values are defined as: 0 ...disable MIM bypass retries 1 - 100 ...retry MIM board un-bypass n times 999 ...retry MIM board un-bypass infinite times Default value is 1.

tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdWrapRetryDelay.name: tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdWrapRetryDelay
tRingMgmtBcnRecBrdWrapRetryDelay.description: This object defines the time delay between wrapping a token ring MIM board left or right due to beaconing and un-wrapping the MIM board to check the state of the board. Setting this object to zero disables retry queue. Non-zero value is delay in seconds with a delay resolution of 1 second.

tRingMgmtRingPollRecovery.name: tRingMgmtRingPollRecovery
tRingMgmtRingPollRecovery.description: This object controls the operation of ring poll failure recovery. A write of disable to this object will cause the ring poll failure recovery process to become inactive on this host. A write of enable will cause the ring poll failure recovery process to become active. If ring poll failure recovery is inoperable on the managing device this object will return `BADSETINFO'. A read of this object will return the current value of this object, reflecting either the last request made or, in the case of a device which is unable to manage ring poll failure recovery, invalid. This object defaults to enabled.

tRingMgmtStnTable.name: tRingMgmtStnTable
tRingMgmtStnTable.description: A list of the stations, by MAC address, participating in the ring poll process of this ring.

tRingMgmtStnEntry.name: tRingMgmtStnEntry
tRingMgmtStnEntry.description: A list of the objects pertaining to a station participating in the ring poll process of this ring.

tRingMgmtStnAddress.name: tRingMgmtStnAddress
tRingMgmtStnAddress.description: Returns the MAC address of the station for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingMgmtStnName.name: tRingMgmtStnName
tRingMgmtStnName.description: An ASCII name assigned to this station.

tRingMgmtStnBoard.name: tRingMgmtStnBoard
tRingMgmtStnBoard.description: Returns the slot number of the Token Ring board this station is connected to. Board numbers are given as 1 thru n. If unknown, a zero is returned.

tRingMgmtStnPort.name: tRingMgmtStnPort
tRingMgmtStnPort.description: Returns the port number of the port on the Token Ring board this station is connected to. Port numbers are given as 1 thru n. If unknown, a zero is returned.

tRingMgmtStnUNA.name: tRingMgmtStnUNA
tRingMgmtStnUNA.description: Returns the address of the station's nearest upstream neighbor. If unknown, the NULL address (00-00-00-00-00-00) is returned.

tRingMgmtStnDNA.name: tRingMgmtStnDNA
tRingMgmtStnDNA.description: Returns the address of the station's nearest downstream neighbor. If unknown, the NULL address (00-00-00-00-00-00) is returned.

tRingMgmtStnPhysLocation.name: tRingMgmtStnPhysLocation
tRingMgmtStnPhysLocation.description: A read of this object returns the physical location of the station. A write of this object assigns a user-defined value indicative of the physical location, or drop, of the station. If the location is unknown or cannot be determined, a zero is returned.

tRingMgmtStnFuncClasses.name: tRingMgmtStnFuncClasses
tRingMgmtStnFuncClasses.description: A read of this object returns the station's enabled function class mask.

tRingMgmtStnPriority.name: tRingMgmtStnPriority
tRingMgmtStnPriority.description: A read of this object returns the station's maximum access priority.

tRingMgmtStnRemoveStn.name: tRingMgmtStnRemoveStn
tRingMgmtStnRemoveStn.description: A write of remove to this object will cause the station to remove itself from the ring. A write of noRemove will do nothing. A read of this object will return the last request made.

tRingMgmtHostCommands.name: tRingMgmtHostCommands
tRingMgmtHostCommands.description: A write to this object performs the indicated command. Either of the reset commands will reset the adapter using default parameters and both imply re-insertion onto the ring. A read of this object will return the last command issued to the adapter.

tRingMgmtHostOpenStatus.name: tRingMgmtHostOpenStatus
tRingMgmtHostOpenStatus.description: A read of this object will return the result of the last open command issued to the adapter.

tRingMgmtHostErrorStatus.name: tRingMgmtHostErrorStatus
tRingMgmtHostErrorStatus.description: A read of this object will return the last error status returned by the adapter. The status is the sum of the applicable error codes listed below: No Problem Detected..................0 Ring Recovery.......................32 Single Station......................64 Counter Overflow...................128 Remove Received....................256 Auto-removal Error................1024 Lobe Wire Fault...................2048 Transmit Beacon...................4096 Soft Error........................8192 Hard Error.......................16384 Signal Loss......................32768 No Status, Open Not Completed...131072

tRingMgmtHostAMContention.name: tRingMgmtHostAMContention
tRingMgmtHostAMContention.description: A write to this object will either allow the adapter to participate in the active monitor contention process or not. A read of this object will return the setting of this object.

tRingMgmtHostTErrorReport.name: tRingMgmtHostTErrorReport
tRingMgmtHostTErrorReport.description: A read of this object returns the host's error report timer value. The default timer value is defined as two seconds by the adapter's manufacturer.

tRingMgmtHostLocalAdminMac.name: tRingMgmtHostLocalAdminMac
tRingMgmtHostLocalAdminMac.description: A read of this object returns the MAC address assigned to the interface attached to this network. A write of this object provides for a locally administered MAC address.

tRingMgmtSecurityAdminState.name: tRingMgmtSecurityAdminState
tRingMgmtSecurityAdminState.description: A write to this object will either disable the security feature, enable Station Added trap being sent, or enable security withecurity feature with the remove station MAC frame being sent in addition to sending the Station Removed trap. A read of this object will return the setting of this object.

tRingMgmtSecurityAddressAdd.name: tRingMgmtSecurityAddressAdd
tRingMgmtSecurityAddressAdd.description: A write to this object will add a station's MAC address to the current secure station list within the device. The source routing bit within the MAC address is ignored. If the security list has reached its maximum number of entries, a BAD_VALUE error is returned. A read of this object will return a MAC address of 00-00-00-00-00-00.

tRingMgmtSecurityAddressRemove.name: tRingMgmtSecurityAddressRemove
tRingMgmtSecurityAddressRemove.description: A write to this object will remove a station's MAC address from the current secure station list within the device. The source routing bit within the MAC address is ignored. If a station is not found on the list, a BAD_VALUE error is returned. A read of this object will return a MAC address of 00-00-00-00-00-00.

tRingMgmtSecurityStnCount.name: tRingMgmtSecurityStnCount
tRingMgmtSecurityStnCount.description: Returns the number of stations on the secure station list.

tRingMgmtSecurityTable.name: tRingMgmtSecurityTable
tRingMgmtSecurityTable.description: The list of secure stations allowed on the ring.

tRingMgmtSecurityEntry.name: tRingMgmtSecurityEntry
tRingMgmtSecurityEntry.description: A list of objects pertaining to a station allowed on this ring.

tRingMgmtSecurityIfIndex.name: tRingMgmtSecurityIfIndex
tRingMgmtSecurityIfIndex.description: A read of this object will return the MIB-II ifIndex to the ring interface the station referenced by this MAC Address was seen on.

tRingMgmtSecurityStnAddress.name: tRingMgmtSecurityStnAddress
tRingMgmtSecurityStnAddress.description: Returns the MAC address of the station on the secure station list

tRingStatsRingFrames.name: tRingStatsRingFrames
tRingStatsRingFrames.description: Returns the total number of all LLC frames that have passed around this ring. If this value cannot be determined, a zero is returned.

tRingStatsRingKBytes.name: tRingStatsRingKBytes
tRingStatsRingKBytes.description: Returns the total number of kilobytes from LLC frames that have passed around this ring. If this value cannot be determined, a zero is returned.

tRingStatsRingLineErrors.name: tRingStatsRingLineErrors
tRingStatsRingLineErrors.description: Returns the total number of line errors that have occurred on this ring.

tRingStatsRingBurstErrors.name: tRingStatsRingBurstErrors
tRingStatsRingBurstErrors.description: Returns the total number of burst errors that have occurred on this ring.

tRingStatsRingACErrors.name: tRingStatsRingACErrors
tRingStatsRingACErrors.description: Returns the total number of address/copied errors that have occurred on this ring.

tRingStatsRingAbortSequences.name: tRingStatsRingAbortSequences
tRingStatsRingAbortSequences.description: Returns the total number of abort sequences that have been transmitted on this ring.

tRingStatsRingInternalErrors.name: tRingStatsRingInternalErrors
tRingStatsRingInternalErrors.description: Returns the number of internal errors that stations on this ring have detected.

tRingStatsRingLostFrames.name: tRingStatsRingLostFrames
tRingStatsRingLostFrames.description: Returns the number of lost frames that have been detected on this ring.

tRingStatsRingCongestErrors.name: tRingStatsRingCongestErrors
tRingStatsRingCongestErrors.description: Returns the number of times stations on this ring have reported receiver congestion errors.

tRingStatsRingFCErrors.name: tRingStatsRingFCErrors
tRingStatsRingFCErrors.description: Returns the number of frame copied errors that have occurred on this ring.

tRingStatsRingTokenErrors.name: tRingStatsRingTokenErrors
tRingStatsRingTokenErrors.description: Returns the number of token errors that have occurred on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFreqErrors.name: tRingStatsRingFreqErrors
tRingStatsRingFreqErrors.description: Returns the total number of frequency errors on this ring.

tRingStatsRingTotalErrors.name: tRingStatsRingTotalErrors
tRingStatsRingTotalErrors.description: This object returns the total number of errors reported by the objects in this table (tRingStatsRingErrs 3 thru tRingStatsRingErrs 12) that have occurred on this ring.

tRingStatsRingAMChanges.name: tRingStatsRingAMChanges
tRingStatsRingAMChanges.description: Returns the number of times the active monitor has changed on this ring.

tRingStatsRingRingPurges.name: tRingStatsRingRingPurges
tRingStatsRingRingPurges.description: Returns the number of times the active monitor has purged the ring.

tRingStatsRingBeaconEvents.name: tRingStatsRingBeaconEvents
tRingStatsRingBeaconEvents.description: Returns the number of times this ring has entered the beaconing state.

tRingStatsRingLongestBeacon.name: tRingStatsRingLongestBeacon
tRingStatsRingLongestBeacon.description: Returns the length of time in TimeTicks of the longest beaconing state on this ring.

tRingStatsRingLastBeacon.name: tRingStatsRingLastBeacon
tRingStatsRingLastBeacon.description: Returns the length of time in TimeTicks of the last beaconing state on this ring.

tRingStatsRingLastBeaconType.name: tRingStatsRingLastBeaconType
tRingStatsRingLastBeaconType.description: Returns the type of beaconing frames last seen on the ring.

tRingStatsRingPollFailureNoRecovery.name: tRingStatsRingPollFailureNoRecovery
tRingStatsRingPollFailureNoRecovery.description: Returns the number of times this ring could not recover from a ring poll failure since the last time this object was reset.

tRingStatsRingPollFailureNNIFrameCount.name: tRingStatsRingPollFailureNNIFrameCount
tRingStatsRingPollFailureNNIFrameCount.description: Returns the number of times this device has detected Neighbor Notification Incomplete MAC frames on the ring since the last time this object was reset

tRingStatsRingPollFailureNNIFrameAddress.name: tRingStatsRingPollFailureNNIFrameAddress
tRingStatsRingPollFailureNNIFrameAddress.description: Returns the MAC address of the ring station that last successfully participated in the ring poll process during and after the ring poll failure process has executed. A value of 00-00-00-00-00-00 indicates that a ring poll has been detected.

tRingStatsRingPollFailureLastNNIFrameTim.name: tRingStatsRingPollFailureLastNNIFrameTime
tRingStatsRingPollFailureLastNNIFrameTim.description: Returns the timestamp of the last time a Neighbor Notification Complete MAC frame was received since the last time this object was reset. A value of zero indicates that no NNI frame was received.

tRingStatsRingPollFailureLastDNAAddress.name: tRingStatsRingPollFailureLastDNAAddress
tRingStatsRingPollFailureLastDNAAddress.description: Returns the last known downstream neighbor MAC address of the ring station that was reported in the Neighbor Notification Incomplete MAC frame. A value of 00-00-00-00-00-00 indicates that no NNI frame was yet received.

tRingStatsRingProtocolSnaFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolSnaFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolSnaFrames.description: Returns the count of SNA frames seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingProtocolXnsFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolXnsFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolXnsFrames.description: Returns the count of XNS frames seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingProtocolTcpIpFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolTcpIpFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolTcpIpFrames.description: Returns the count of TCP/IP frames seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingProtocolBanyanFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolBanyanFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolBanyanFrames.description: Returns the count of Banyan frames seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingProtocolIpxFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolIpxFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolIpxFrames.description: Returns the count of Novell IPX frames seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingProtocolNetbiosFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolNetbiosFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolNetbiosFrames.description: Returns the count of NetBIOS frames seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingProtocolLanNetMgrFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolLanNetMgrFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolLanNetMgrFrames.description: Returns the count of LAN Network Manager frames seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingProtocolOtherFrames.name: tRingStatsRingProtocolOtherFrames
tRingStatsRingProtocolOtherFrames.description: Returns the count of all other frame types seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesizeUpTo63Bytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesizeUpTo63Bytes
tRingStatsRingFramesizeUpTo63Bytes.description: Returns the count of frames less than 64 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesize64To127Bytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesize64To127Bytes
tRingStatsRingFramesize64To127Bytes.description: Returns the count of frames between 64 bytes and 127 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesize128To255Bytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesize128To255Bytes
tRingStatsRingFramesize128To255Bytes.description: Returns the count of frames between 128 bytes and 255 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesize256To511Bytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesize256To511Bytes
tRingStatsRingFramesize256To511Bytes.description: Returns the count of frames between 256 bytes and 511 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesize512To1023Bytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesize512To1023Bytes
tRingStatsRingFramesize512To1023Bytes.description: Returns the count of frames between 512 bytes and 1023 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesize1024To2047Bytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesize1024To2047Bytes
tRingStatsRingFramesize1024To2047Bytes.description: Returns the count of frames between 1024 bytes and 2047 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesize2048To4095Bytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesize2048To4095Bytes
tRingStatsRingFramesize2048To4095Bytes.description: Returns the count of frames between 2048 bytes and 4095 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsRingFramesize4096AndUpBytes.name: tRingStatsRingFramesize4096AndUpBytes
tRingStatsRingFramesize4096AndUpBytes.description: Returns the count of frames greater than 4096 bytes in size seen on this ring.

tRingStatsStnTable.name: tRingStatsStnTable
tRingStatsStnTable.description: A list of statistical objects reported by the stations participating in the ring poll process of this ring.

tRingStatsStnEntry.name: tRingStatsStnEntry
tRingStatsStnEntry.description: A list of statistical objects reported by a station which is participating in the ring poll process of this ring.

tRingStatsStnAddress.name: tRingStatsStnAddress
tRingStatsStnAddress.description: Returns the MAC address to the station port for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingStatsStnFrames.name: tRingStatsStnFrames
tRingStatsStnFrames.description: This object returns the total number of LLC frames that have originated from this station.

tRingStatsStnBytes.name: tRingStatsStnBytes
tRingStatsStnBytes.description: Returns the total number of bytes from all LLC frames that have originated from this station.

tRingStatsStnLineErrors.name: tRingStatsStnLineErrors
tRingStatsStnLineErrors.description: This object gives the number of line errors that have been detected by the station.

tRingStatsStnBurstErrors.name: tRingStatsStnBurstErrors
tRingStatsStnBurstErrors.description: This object gives the number of burst errors that have been detected by the station.

tRingStatsStnACErrors.name: tRingStatsStnACErrors
tRingStatsStnACErrors.description: Returns the total number of address/copied errors that that have been detected by the station.

tRingStatsStnAbortSequences.name: tRingStatsStnAbortSequences
tRingStatsStnAbortSequences.description: This object gives the number of abort sequences that have been sent by the station.

tRingStatsStnInternalErrors.name: tRingStatsStnInternalErrors
tRingStatsStnInternalErrors.description: This object gives the number of internal errors that have been detected by the station.

tRingStatsStnLostFrames.name: tRingStatsStnLostFrames
tRingStatsStnLostFrames.description: This object gives the number of lost frames that have been detected by the station.

tRingStatsStnCongestErrors.name: tRingStatsStnCongestErrors
tRingStatsStnCongestErrors.description: This object gives the number of congestion errors that have been occurred at the station.

tRingStatsStnFCErrors.name: tRingStatsStnFCErrors
tRingStatsStnFCErrors.description: This object gives the number of frame copied errors that have been detected by the station.

tRingStatsStnTokenErrors.name: tRingStatsStnTokenErrors
tRingStatsStnTokenErrors.description: This object gives the number of token errors that have been detected by the station while it was acting as the active monitor.

tRingStatsStnFreqErrors.name: tRingStatsStnFreqErrors
tRingStatsStnFreqErrors.description: This object gives the number of frequency errors that have been detected by the station.

tRingStatsStnErrors.name: tRingStatsStnErrors
tRingStatsStnErrors.description: This object returns the sum of all errors reported by this table (tRingStatsStnEntry 4 thru tRingStatsStnEntry 13) that have been detected by this station.

tRingStatsResetCounters.name: tRingStatsResetCounters
tRingStatsResetCounters.description: This object, when written with the value resetCounters, would reset all of this MIB's counter objects associated with the stations on this ring. This in turn resets all of this MIB's counter objects associated with this ring. Writing this object with the value noResetCounters has no effect. When read, this object returns noResetCounters.

tRingStatsResetTime.name: tRingStatsResetTime
tRingStatsResetTime.description: This object reports the time in TimeTicks that this ring's statistical counters were last reset via the tRingStatsResetCounters command. If the counters have not been reset, this value is zero.

tRingAlarmsRingTimebase.name: tRingAlarmsRingTimebase
tRingAlarmsRingTimebase.description: Get/Set alarm timebase. This timebase is used for all alarms pertaining to this ring (including station alarms). Measured in seconds. Minimum interval (default)...10 secs.

tRingAlarmsRingRingPurgesEnable.name: tRingAlarmsRingRingPurgesEnable
tRingAlarmsRingRingPurgesEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Ring Purges threshold alarm. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsRingAMPErrsEnable.name: tRingAlarmsRingAMPErrsEnable
tRingAlarmsRingAMPErrsEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Active Monitor Error threshold alarm. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsRingTokenErrsEnable.name: tRingAlarmsRingTokenErrsEnable
tRingAlarmsRingTokenErrsEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Token Errors threshold alarm. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsRingClaimTknErrsEnable.name: tRingAlarmsRingClaimTknErrsEnable
tRingAlarmsRingClaimTknErrsEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Claim Token Errors threshold alarm. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsRingLostFramesEnable.name: tRingAlarmsRingLostFramesEnable
tRingAlarmsRingLostFramesEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Lost Frames threshold alarm. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsRingBeaconStateEnable.name: tRingAlarmsRingBeaconStateEnable
tRingAlarmsRingBeaconStateEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Beacon State threshold alarm. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsRingFrameCountEnable.name: tRingAlarmsRingFrameCountEnable
tRingAlarmsRingFrameCountEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the total Frame Count threshold alarm. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsRingRingPurgesThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsRingRingPurgesThreshold
tRingAlarmsRingRingPurgesThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Ring Purges. Valid ranges are 1 to 36000 with a default value of 70.

tRingAlarmsRingAMPErrsThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsRingAMPErrsThreshold
tRingAlarmsRingAMPErrsThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Active Monitor Errors. Valid ranges are 1 to 1800 with a default value of 1.

tRingAlarmsRingTokenErrsThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsRingTokenErrsThreshold
tRingAlarmsRingTokenErrsThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Token Errors. Valid ranges are 5 to 7200 with a default value of 10.

tRingAlarmsRingClaimTknThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsRingClaimTknThreshold
tRingAlarmsRingClaimTknThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Claim Tokens. Valid ranges are 1 to 7200 with a default value of 5.

tRingAlarmsRingLostFramesThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsRingLostFramesThreshold
tRingAlarmsRingLostFramesThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Lost Frames. Valid ranges are 5 to 7200 with a default value of 10.

tRingAlarmsRingBeaconStateThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsRingBeaconStateThreshold
tRingAlarmsRingBeaconStateThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Beacon States. Valid ranges are 1 to 7200 with a default value of 1.

tRingAlarmsRingFrameCountThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsRingFrameCountThreshold
tRingAlarmsRingFrameCountThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for the total Frame Count. Valid ranges are 2430 to 250000 with a default values of 8920 for 4 Mbps and 33890 for 16 Mbps ring speeds.

tRingAlarmsStnEnblTable.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblTable
tRingAlarmsStnEnblTable.description: A list of alarm enabling objects pertaining to the stations participating in the ring poll process on this ring.

tRingAlarmsStnEnblEntry.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblEntry
tRingAlarmsStnEnblEntry.description: A list of alarm enabling objects pertaining to a station participating in the ring poll process on this ring.

tRingAlarmsStnEnblAddress.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblAddress
tRingAlarmsStnEnblAddress.description: Returns the address of the station to which the information in this table pertains.

tRingAlarmsStnEnblLineErrsEnable.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblLineErrsEnable
tRingAlarmsStnEnblLineErrsEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Line Errors threshold alarm for this station. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsStnEnblInternalErrsEnable.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblInternalErrsEnable
tRingAlarmsStnEnblInternalErrsEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Internal Errors threshold alarm for this station. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsStnEnblBurstErrsEnable.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblBurstErrsEnable
tRingAlarmsStnEnblBurstErrsEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Burst Errors threshold alarm for this station. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsStnEnblACErrsEnable.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblACErrsEnable
tRingAlarmsStnEnblACErrsEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Address Recognized/Frame Copied Errors threshold alarm for this station. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsStnEnblRcvrCongestEnable.name: tRingAlarmsStnEnblRcvrCongestEnable
tRingAlarmsStnEnblRcvrCongestEnable.description: A write of value 2 will enable the Receiver Congestion threshold alarm for this station. A write of value 1 will disable this threshold alarm (default).

tRingAlarmsStnThrshTable.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshTable
tRingAlarmsStnThrshTable.description: A list of threshold alarm objects pertaining to the stations participating in the ring poll process on this ring.

tRingAlarmsStnThrshEntry.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshEntry
tRingAlarmsStnThrshEntry.description: A list of threshold alarm objects pertaining to a station participating in the ring poll process on this ring.

tRingAlarmsStnThrshAddress.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshAddress
tRingAlarmsStnThrshAddress.description: Returns the address of the station to which the information in this table pertains.

tRingAlarmsStnThrshLineErrsThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshLineErrsThreshold
tRingAlarmsStnThrshLineErrsThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Line Errors. Valid ranges are 1 to 3600 with a default value of 2.

tRingAlarmsStnThrshInternalErrsThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshInternalErrsThreshold
tRingAlarmsStnThrshInternalErrsThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Internal Errors. Valid ranges are 1 to 3600 with a default value of 1.

tRingAlarmsStnThrshBurstErrsThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshBurstErrsThreshold
tRingAlarmsStnThrshBurstErrsThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Burst Errors. Valid ranges are 5 to 18000 with a default value of 10.

tRingAlarmsStnThrshACErrsThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshACErrsThreshold
tRingAlarmsStnThrshACErrsThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Address Recognized/Frame Copied Errors. Valid ranges are 1 to 1800 with a default value of 2.

tRingAlarmsStnThrshRcvrCongestThreshold.name: tRingAlarmsStnThrshRcvrCongestThreshold
tRingAlarmsStnThrshRcvrCongestThreshold.description: The threshold alarm value for Receiver Congestion Errors. Valid ranges are 1 to 90000 with a default value of 124.

tRingPortGrpTable.name: tRingPortGrpTable
tRingPortGrpTable.description: A list of port group management objects which pertains to a collection of port groups making up this ring.

tRingPortGrpEntry.name: tRingPortGrpEntry
tRingPortGrpEntry.description: A list of port group management objects which pertains to a single instance of a port group residing on this ring.

tRingPortGrpId.name: tRingPortGrpId
tRingPortGrpId.description: Returns an index to a port group for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingPortGrpName.name: tRingPortGrpName
tRingPortGrpName.description: An ASCII name assigned to this port group. The default name is Board n', where n is a number 1 through n.

tRingPortGrpStnPortCount.name: tRingPortGrpStnPortCount
tRingPortGrpStnPortCount.description: This object defines the total number of station ports on the addressed board.

tRingPortGrpRingPortCount.name: tRingPortGrpRingPortCount
tRingPortGrpRingPortCount.description: This object defines the total number of ring ports (ring-in or ring-out) on the addressed board.

tRingPortGrpStnPortsEnable.name: tRingPortGrpStnPortsEnable
tRingPortGrpStnPortsEnable.description: Setting this object to enable will cause all the station ports in this port group to be enabled. Setting this object to noEnable will have no effect on the station ports in this port group. When read this object will always return noEnable.

tRingPortGrpRingPortsEnable.name: tRingPortGrpRingPortsEnable
tRingPortGrpRingPortsEnable.description: Setting this object to enable will cause all the ring ports in this port group to be enabled. Setting this object to noEnable will have no effect on the ring ports in this port group. When read this object will always return noEnable.

tRingPortGrpStnPortsOn.name: tRingPortGrpStnPortsOn
tRingPortGrpStnPortsOn.description: Returns the total number of enabled station ports in this port group.

tRingPortGrpRingPortsOn.name: tRingPortGrpRingPortsOn
tRingPortGrpRingPortsOn.description: Returns the total number of enabled ring in/out ports in this port group.

tRingPortGrpMode.name: tRingPortGrpMode
tRingPortGrpMode.description: This object defines the mode of the board. In Auto Mode, the board is using its hardware defaults. The default values of the board are all ports enabled, speed selected by the HW jumper on the board, the FNB attempts to attach left and right and not bypassed, ring port phantom current (if applicable) is controlled via a HW switch, and selectable media (if applicable) is managed also via a HW switch. In Management Mode, the hardware defaults may be overridden by network or local management.

tRingPortGrpSpeed.name: tRingPortGrpSpeed
tRingPortGrpSpeed.description: This object sets the speed of the board. On devices with a MAC interface this object is read-only, and will return NO SUCH NAME on write requests.

tRingPortGrpSpeedFault.name: tRingPortGrpSpeedFault
tRingPortGrpSpeedFault.description: This object reports a ring speed fault.

tRingPortGrpSpeedFaultLocation.name: tRingPortGrpSpeedFaultLocation
tRingPortGrpSpeedFaultLocation.description: This object indicates the last ring speed fault detection circuit(s) to detect the fault, if there was one.

tRingPortGrpBypassRingPortState.name: tRingPortGrpBypassRingPortState
tRingPortGrpBypassRingPortState.description: This object sets and reports the state of the ring bypass relay on those token ring boards which support the relay.

tRingPortMgmtTable.name: tRingPortMgmtTable
tRingPortMgmtTable.description: A list of port management objects which pertains to a collection of ports in a port group residing on this ring.

tRingPortMgmtEntry.name: tRingPortMgmtEntry
tRingPortMgmtEntry.description: A list of port management objects which pertains to a single instance of a port in a port group residing on this ring.

tRingPortMgmtPortId.name: tRingPortMgmtPortId
tRingPortMgmtPortId.description: Returns an index to a port for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingPortMgmtPortGrpId.name: tRingPortMgmtPortGrpId
tRingPortMgmtPortGrpId.description: Returns an index to a port group to which the port belongs for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingPortMgmtPortName.name: tRingPortMgmtPortName
tRingPortMgmtPortName.description: Gets/Sets an ASCII name for this port. The default name for this object is 'Board b, Port p', where b and p are integers 1 through n.

tRingPortMgmtPortAdminState.name: tRingPortMgmtPortAdminState
tRingPortMgmtPortAdminState.description: Setting this object to enable will cause the port to be enabled. Setting this object to disable will cause the ports to be disabled. When read this object will always return the state of the last request.

tRingPortMgmtPortOperState.name: tRingPortMgmtPortOperState
tRingPortMgmtPortOperState.description: Returns the operational state of this port.

tRingPortMgmtPortType.name: tRingPortMgmtPortType
tRingPortMgmtPortType.description: Uniquely defines the station or ring port type. An authoritative identification for a token ring station or ring port type. By convention, this value is allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree (1.3.6.1.4.1), and provides an easy and unambiguous means to determine the type of a token ring station or ring port.

tRingPortMgmtSpeedFaultDetect.name: tRingPortMgmtSpeedFaultDetect
tRingPortMgmtSpeedFaultDetect.description: This object indicates whether a speed fault has been detected at this port. If the HW is incapable of detecting a speed fault at the port, the value notDetectable is returned.

tRingPortMgmtRingOutEnable.name: tRingPortMgmtRingOutEnable
tRingPortMgmtRingOutEnable.description: This object, when written, permits the port to function as either a ring out port or a station port, if available. If this selection is not supported by this port, then any write to this object will return a BADSETINFO error. When read, this object will return the state of the port with respect to this mode of operation. The default state of this object, if available, is disabled; otherwise it is notAvailable.

tRingPortStnTable.name: tRingPortStnTable
tRingPortStnTable.description: A list of station port management objects which pertains to a collection of station ports in a port group residing on this ring.

tRingPortStnEntry.name: tRingPortStnEntry
tRingPortStnEntry.description: A list of station port management objects which pertains to a single instance of a station port in a port group residing on this ring.

tRingPortStnPortId.name: tRingPortStnPortId
tRingPortStnPortId.description: Returns an index to a port for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingPortStnPortGrpId.name: tRingPortStnPortGrpId
tRingPortStnPortGrpId.description: Returns an index to a port group to which the port belongs for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingPortStnPortLinkState.name: tRingPortStnPortLinkState
tRingPortStnPortLinkState.description: This object reports the link status of a port. The link status indicates the port is detecting a good phantom current.

tRingPortStnPortLinkStateTime.name: tRingPortStnPortLinkStateTime
tRingPortStnPortLinkStateTime.description: This object reports the amount of time in TimeTicks since the port's link state last changed.

tRingPortStnPortMapEnable.name: tRingPortStnPortMapEnable
tRingPortStnPortMapEnable.description: A write of mappingEnabled to this object permits a station port to be associated, or mapped, to a station participating in the ring poll process on this ring. A write of mappingDisabled prevents this association from taking place. This object is intended to be used when a network monitoring device, such as Network General's Sniffer (tm), is inserted on a ring but is not actively participating in the ring poll. The default value of this object is mappingEnabled.

tRingPortStnPortMappedMacAddr.name: tRingPortStnPortMappedMacAddr
tRingPortStnPortMappedMacAddr.description: This object reports the MAC address of the station mapped to this port, if known. If unknown, the NULL address is returned.

tRingPortStnInsertionTrapEnable.name: tRingPortStnInsertionTrapEnable
tRingPortStnInsertionTrapEnable.description: A write of enabled to this object permits the port inserted and port deinserted traps to be sent when phantom current has been asserted or removed, respectively, on this station port. A write of disabled prevents the traps from being sent. The default state of this object is disabled.

tRingPortRingTable.name: tRingPortRingTable
tRingPortRingTable.description: A list of ring port management objects which pertains to a collection of ring ports in a port group residing on this ring.

tRingPortRingEntry.name: tRingPortRingEntry
tRingPortRingEntry.description: A list of ring port management objects which pertains to a single instance of a ring port in a port group residing on this ring.

tRingPortRingPortId.name: tRingPortRingPortId
tRingPortRingPortId.description: Returns an index to a port for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingPortRingPortGrpId.name: tRingPortRingPortGrpId
tRingPortRingPortGrpId.description: Returns an index to a port group to which the port belongs for which the information in this table pertains.

tRingPortRingPortClass.name: tRingPortRingPortClass
tRingPortRingPortClass.description: This object returns a code indicating whether the queried ring port is capable of either autowrapping or not, or whether the media type is selectable (implies autowrappability).

tRingPortRingPortMediaSelect.name: tRingPortRingPortMediaSelect
tRingPortRingPortMediaSelect.description: When written, this object allows for the selection of the media type for this ring port. If the ring port is not selectable and an attempt is made to change the media type, a BADSETINFO error will be returned. When read, this object will return the last selection made unless it is unselectable, in which case noSelection is returned.

tRingPortRingFaultStatus.name: tRingPortRingFaultStatus
tRingPortRingFaultStatus.description: This object reports the media fault status of a ring port capable of auto-wrapping.

tRingPortRingFaultStateTime.name: tRingPortRingFaultStateTime
tRingPortRingFaultStateTime.description: This object reports the amount of time in TimeTicks since the ring port fault state last changed.

tRingPortRingPhantomCurrent.name: tRingPortRingPhantomCurrent
tRingPortRingPhantomCurrent.description: When written with the value activatePhantom, this object activates the board's phantom current for the ring port, if applicable. This may be different from the HW switch setting. When written with the value deactivatePhantom, the board removes phantom current for this port, if applicable. This may be different from the HW switch setting. If the port does not support phantom drive, any write to this object will return a BADSETINFO error. When read, this object reports the state of the ring port's phantom drive status, whether enabled, disabled, or not supported.

tRingPortRingPortType.name: tRingPortRingPortType
tRingPortRingPortType.description: This object reports the ring port type.

tRingIfIndex.name: tRingIfIndex
tRingIfIndex.description: A read of this object will return the MIB-II ifIndex to the interface this ring is attached to.
